  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-4ccdf3bb-7fff-9cab-6997-421c4780b08b&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The proposal by reason of its design, scale, location, and siting would be visually detrimental to the character and appearance of the host building and the street scene and would harm the setting of the locally listed buildings that it forms part of. It would neither preserve nor enhance the character and appearance of the conservation area. As such the proposal is contrary to LP1 (High quality design), LP3 (Designated heritage assets), and LP4 (Non designated heritage assets) of Hackney Local Plan 2033, and policies &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-9203652e-7fff-2f45-ad86-485ecf3393ae&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;D3 (Optimising site capacity through the design-led approach), &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; font-family: Arial; font-size: 11pt; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;D4 (Delivering good design) and HC1 (Heritage conservation and growth) of the London Plan 2021; Paragraphs 130, 134, 197, and 199 of the NPPF and the De Beauvoir Conservation Area Appraisal. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
